cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with predicting the future location of users in wireless networks, which can be considered as a social network. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the quality of service perceived by clients in wireless networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a cluster-aided predictor that relies on clustering techniques, which is a common approach in machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper presents a predictive model that uses past trajectories to predict the future location of users, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses non-parametric Bayesian statistical tools to design the cluster-aided predictor, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures.
